abstract: >-
  The Thiele Machine is a formally verified computational model that treats structural
  information as a costly resource. It includes machine-checked proofs in Coq (238 files,
  zero admits), a Python reference VM, and synthesizable Verilog hardware. The model
  introduces the Î¼-bit as an atomic unit of structural cost and proves the No Free
  Insight theorem: you cannot narrow the search space without paying the information-
  theoretic cost of that narrowing. Built by a self-taught developer with no formal
  CS background, demonstrating that modern tools make formal methods accessible to
  anyone willing to learn.

